    <div class="ref-card">
      <h3>Sarcomere <em>Anatomy</em></h3>
      <div class="key-term"><strong>Z-lines</strong><span>Boundaries of each sarcomere. Pulled closer together during contraction.</span></div>
      <div class="key-term"><strong>H Zone</strong><span>Center of sarcomere. Contains ONLY myosin — no actin extends here. Lighter in color.</span></div>
      <div class="key-term"><strong>M Line</strong><span>Thin line crossing center of H zone.</span></div>
      <div class="key-term"><strong>I Band</strong><span>Contains actin only — no myosin overlap. Lightens as muscle contracts.</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="ref-card">
      <h3>Double-Progression <em>Protocol</em></h3>
      <div class="key-term"><strong>Step 1 — Add Reps</strong><span>Work within a rep range (e.g., 8–12). Add one rep per session until top of range achieved with good form.</span></div>
      <div class="key-term"><strong>Step 2 — Add Weight</strong><span>Once top of range achieved → increase resistance by ~5%. Reset to bottom of rep range.</span></div>
      <div class="key-term"><strong>No Time Limit</strong><span>Whether it takes 1 week or 1 month — weight increases only when earned with proper form.</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

